         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot Garden ¶ 15/5/71 ¶  ¶ Let me in first instance express my extreme gratification, dear Mr Guilfoyle, in seeing my name connected with your natural magnificent Park, a honor which I all th...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.05.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Michael Guilfoyle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS 439c, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/5/71</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me in first instance express my extreme gratification, dear Mr Guilfoyle, in seeing my name connected with your natural magnificent Park, a honor which I all the more prize as the landscape is so grand on the Tweed and as I have really so little claim on your consideration.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Guilfoyle, appreciative of the interest M was taking in his son William, decided to name an area of the settlement of Cudgen at his plantation on the Tweed River in honour of M. His doing so was never, however, officially registered. See R. Pescott (1974), p. 52.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have utilized the <name key="Strangea">Strangea</name> and shown that Bentham is wrong in uniting that genus with <name key="Grevillea">Grevillea</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863-78), vol. 5, p. 453.</p>
               </note> and that the W.A. genus <name key="Molloya">Molloya</name> belongs to <name key="Strangea">Strangea</name> also as a second species.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M treated <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Molloya">Molloya</name>
                     </seg> as a synonym of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Strangea">Strangea</name>
                     </seg> in B71.07.01, p. 131.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope you will allow a good deal of the best and grandest native vegetation to remain in its pristine state in your Park</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many grateful acknowledgements for your invitation. Some day later in life, if providence spares me, I hope to avail myself of it</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Sarcochilus, sent some time ago, is S. Fitzgeraldi. The Mappa will be M. tanaria. I know it from several parts of QL.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
